1
00:00:09,623 --> 00:00:10,833
Haah...

2
00:00:12,294 --> 00:00:14,507
Sorry I'm late.

3
00:00:15,050 --> 00:00:17,012
You're already late.

4
00:00:17,471 --> 00:00:18,515
Here.

5
00:00:18,766 --> 00:00:21,187
Huh? What's this?

6
00:00:25,529 --> 00:00:27,533
Ah, hey!

7
00:00:27,909 --> 00:00:31,040
Please don't open it until you have all seven.

8
00:00:31,123 --> 00:00:33,461
Wha... so what?

9
00:00:33,545 --> 00:00:35,465
I'll contact you when you have them all.

10
00:00:36,175 --> 00:00:37,637
It's a promise.

11
00:00:38,179 --> 00:00:39,473
Yumi-san!

12
00:00:40,225 --> 00:00:43,732
Yumi-san! Yumi-san!

13
00:00:44,316 --> 00:00:45,987
Assistant Inspector Miyamoto Yumi!

14
00:00:46,237 --> 00:00:47,532
Hah...

15
00:00:48,157 --> 00:00:52,457
Come on, please don't doze off during patrol.

16
00:00:52,542 --> 00:00:54,504
(Yawn)

17
00:00:54,838 --> 00:01:00,850
♪~♪

18
00:01:07,864 --> 00:01:11,078
The blackness of shadows, the density of darkness—
the light of reasoning cuts right through them.

19
00:01:11,162 --> 00:01:14,878
Assistant Inspector Yumi Miyamoto's secret?
A new character appears with sharp deductions.

20
00:01:15,504 --> 00:01:16,798
See through the one and only truth.

21
00:01:16,882 --> 00:01:18,802
Looks like a kid, but has the mind of an adult.

22
00:01:18,886 --> 00:01:21,600
His name is Detective Conan!

23
00:02:43,555 --> 00:02:49,567
♪~♪

24
00:02:53,446 --> 00:02:58,946
"The Neighbor at the Site is an Ex-Boyfriend (Part 1)"

25
00:02:58,946 --> 00:02:59,946
(Yawn)

26
00:03:01,626 --> 00:03:04,842
Yumi-san, did something happen last night?

27
00:03:04,925 --> 00:03:06,177
Sorry.

28
00:03:06,261 --> 00:03:09,434
I played mahjong all night with some detectives from the Violent Crimes unit.

29
00:03:09,517 --> 00:03:13,692
Staying up all night playing mahjong isn't good for you. For your work or your skin.

30
00:03:13,775 --> 00:03:14,820
Yeah, yeah.

31
00:03:15,321 --> 00:03:18,285
More importantly, what is this about "when you have all seven"?

32
00:03:18,368 --> 00:03:20,664
Gah... Did I say that?

33
00:03:20,916 --> 00:03:25,341
Yes. In your sleep, you said things like "When will that ever be complete?"

34
00:03:25,424 --> 00:03:26,801
Haah... Hmm?

35
00:03:27,553 --> 00:03:29,641
It's something my ex-boyfriend said.

36
00:03:29,724 --> 00:03:32,730
When I said, "I'm becoming a police officer, so let's break up,"

37
00:03:32,814 --> 00:03:36,864
he forced this strange envelope on me and said, "Wait until I have all seven."

38
00:03:36,948 --> 00:03:38,325
Huh...

39
00:03:38,408 --> 00:03:42,750
But he never once contacted me, so I dumped him.

40
00:03:42,834 --> 00:03:45,214
I couldn't wait anymore, and I didn't want to see his face

41
00:03:45,297 --> 00:03:47,218
or hear his voice.

42
00:03:47,301 --> 00:03:49,639
So... where did you meet him?

43
00:03:49,722 --> 00:03:52,520
In a train, when I was in college.

44
00:03:52,603 --> 00:03:55,526
He lived in a nice area, so maybe he was some rich kid?

45
00:03:55,609 --> 00:03:58,866
But what were those "seven" things?

46
00:03:58,950 --> 00:04:01,371
Who knows? Probably something stupid...

47
00:04:01,454 --> 00:04:04,168
Was he a sailor?

48
00:04:04,837 --> 00:04:09,012
He wanted you to wait until he conquered

49
00:04:09,095 --> 00:04:13,687
the seven seas: the North Atlantic, South Atlantic, North Pacific,

50
00:04:13,770 --> 00:04:16,819
South Pacific, Indian Ocean, Arctic Ocean, and Antarctic Ocean.

51
00:04:16,902 --> 00:04:18,906
Co... Conan-kun.

52
00:04:19,115 --> 00:04:21,244
Was he tanned?

53
00:04:21,327 --> 00:04:25,502
No, he was pale. He looked like a shut-in NEET.

54
00:04:25,586 --> 00:04:27,883
He seemed to go out often,

55
00:04:27,966 --> 00:04:30,804
but it was irregular, and it didn't look like work.

56
00:04:31,056 --> 00:04:33,936
Then maybe he was visiting the Seven Gods of Fortune?

57
00:04:34,020 --> 00:04:37,276
That's the thing where you go around to shrines and temples on New Year's

58
00:04:37,359 --> 00:04:40,115
and collect the seven deity dolls, right?

59
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:42,661
My mom does that every year.

60
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:45,250
That would be complete quickly, wouldn't it?

61
00:04:45,334 --> 00:04:49,801
Another possibility is the Seven Deadly Sins.

62
00:04:49,968 --> 00:04:51,763
Huh? Hmm?

63
00:04:52,046 --> 00:04:55,846
Pride, envy, wrath, sloth,

64
00:04:55,846 --> 00:04:59,746
greed, gluttony, and lust.

65
00:04:59,746 --> 00:05:00,746
...the seven sins.

66
00:05:00,746 --> 00:05:02,284
What would anyone do with those?

67
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:05,959
But the Seven Gods of Fortune might be possible.

68
00:05:06,042 --> 00:05:08,171
He told me that on Christmas, after all.

69
00:05:08,588 --> 00:05:12,221
...Why am I even telling you kids all this?

70
00:05:12,304 --> 00:05:14,142
Ahahaha... Geez.

71
00:05:14,225 --> 00:05:16,856
So what happened to that envelope?

72
00:05:17,189 --> 00:05:19,402
That thing? It ended up somewhere.

73
00:05:19,485 --> 00:05:21,781
You're the one who crashed into me!

74
00:05:22,324 --> 00:05:23,660
What did you say?

75
00:05:23,743 --> 00:05:24,913
You got a problem?

76
00:05:24,997 --> 00:05:27,501
Could you back up and pull over to the shoulder?

77
00:05:27,585 --> 00:05:28,753
Ah, yes.

78
00:05:29,255 --> 00:05:32,094
Hey. What do you two think you're doing?

79
00:05:38,773 --> 00:05:39,902
Phew...

80
00:05:40,736 --> 00:05:43,241
Yumi-san had a boyfriend?

81
00:05:44,493 --> 00:05:47,041
Strangely, it doesn't feel like the first time...

82
00:05:47,124 --> 00:05:48,126
Huh?

83
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,464
Seeing you.

84
00:05:51,090 --> 00:05:53,470
You, by any chance...

85
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,474
Ah, yes.

86
00:05:56,476 --> 00:06:00,734
You're the one who gave me a parking ticket in Haido Town the other day.

87
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:04,742
You've completely forgotten, haven't you, Chiba-kun?

88
00:06:06,412 --> 00:06:08,625
Don't cross! Huh?

89
00:06:09,126 --> 00:06:11,631
Once you spoil yourself and break a rule,

90
00:06:11,714 --> 00:06:13,134
it becomes a habit.

91
00:06:13,677 --> 00:06:16,391
Even if you want to stop a habit, you can't.

92
00:06:16,766 --> 00:06:19,105
Don't you understand that?

93
00:06:19,188 --> 00:06:20,858
Ugh...

94
00:06:20,942 --> 00:06:26,661
Ah... (Young Naeko crying)

95
00:06:26,744 --> 00:06:30,669
(Cell phone rings) Hmm?

96
00:06:30,752 --> 00:06:33,174
Ah... from Sakurako?

97
00:06:33,843 --> 00:06:37,016
What? I'm at work right now.

98
00:06:37,641 --> 00:06:39,645
Huh? Someone died?

99
00:06:40,605 --> 00:06:43,445
B-but I'm not a detective...

100
00:06:43,988 --> 00:06:46,117
Hey, is that nearby?

101
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,411
Uh... yes.

102
00:06:49,623 --> 00:06:50,667
Hmm?

103
00:06:52,254 --> 00:06:53,673
Hey, listen...

104
00:06:53,924 --> 00:06:56,930
Anyway, don't touch anything. I'll be there soon.

105
00:06:57,014 --> 00:06:59,185
What's with those kids? They looked pale...

106
00:06:59,268 --> 00:07:02,566
I just got a call from my friend saying someone died.

107
00:07:02,649 --> 00:07:04,278
Huh? Where?

108
00:07:04,362 --> 00:07:06,449
At the Chateau Beika Mansion near here.

109
00:07:06,532 --> 00:07:10,958
Ah, Cha... Chateau Beika Mansion?

110
00:07:13,004 --> 00:07:14,715
So it was here.

111
00:07:14,966 --> 00:07:17,847
Um, have you been here before?

112
00:07:17,931 --> 00:07:19,058
No, I haven't.

113
00:07:19,308 --> 00:07:22,564
A mansion like this where only rich people live.

114
00:07:23,859 --> 00:07:27,658
Ah, Miyamoto-sama! Long time no see.

115
00:07:29,495 --> 00:07:30,664
Hello.

116
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:33,586
You have been here before, haven't you?

117
00:07:33,670 --> 00:07:35,048
Shut up.

118
00:07:39,098 --> 00:07:41,269
So... which floor?

119
00:07:41,352 --> 00:07:43,189
The 18th floor. Huh?

120
00:07:43,481 --> 00:07:46,737
No way, no way...

121
00:07:49,285 --> 00:07:51,164
What, so he was my neighbor?

122
00:07:51,247 --> 00:07:52,249
Haah...

123
00:07:52,332 --> 00:07:54,336
Oh, the mini-patrol ladies are here too?

124
00:07:54,420 --> 00:07:56,090
Huh?

125
00:07:56,340 --> 00:07:59,848
Huh? But Yumi-san, you're with the Traffic Division.

126
00:07:59,931 --> 00:08:02,227
This kind of case isn't really your jurisdiction...

127
00:08:02,311 --> 00:08:03,856
Leave it to us.

128
00:08:03,939 --> 00:08:06,235
You guys aren't in jurisdiction either.

129
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:08,740
I just came to bring you kids back...

130
00:08:08,824 --> 00:08:10,202
Huh? Hmm?

131
00:08:10,452 --> 00:08:11,955
But Conan-kun isn't here...

132
00:08:12,039 --> 00:08:13,082
He's inside.

133
00:08:13,166 --> 00:08:15,253
He told us to wait out here.

134
00:08:15,337 --> 00:08:17,508
No way, he went inside?

135
00:08:18,551 --> 00:08:21,307
Who is this boy?

136
00:08:21,682 --> 00:08:23,394
Is he someone the housekeeper knows?

137
00:08:23,603 --> 00:08:26,902
Ah, yes. I believe his name is...

138
00:08:26,985 --> 00:08:28,279
Edogawa Conan.

139
00:08:28,906 --> 00:08:31,744
We met at the scene of a murder case before.

140
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,665
Sakurako Yonehara-san.

141
00:08:33,748 --> 00:08:37,256
Uh... yes. During that optical illusion case.

142
00:08:37,756 --> 00:08:39,426
Hey, little boy.

143
00:08:39,510 --> 00:08:42,307
Isn't your way of speaking different from earlier?

144
00:08:42,391 --> 00:08:46,440
Because when you were with everyone else, you acted like a normal kid, but

145
00:08:46,732 --> 00:08:49,113
now you sound just like a detective.

146
00:08:49,196 --> 00:08:50,825
Ah, no, that's...

147
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:53,788
I've been working as a live-out housekeeper here

148
00:08:53,872 --> 00:08:55,792
since last week, but...

149
00:08:55,876 --> 00:08:57,337
again, something like this...

150
00:08:57,421 --> 00:08:58,798
Sa... Sakurako.

151
00:08:58,882 --> 00:09:00,260
Ah, Nae-chan.

152
00:09:00,552 --> 00:09:04,685
Sorry, I panicked and called Nae-chan without thinking.

153
00:09:04,768 --> 00:09:07,316
It's okay. We called the detectives.

154
00:09:07,399 --> 00:09:08,526
Haah...

155
00:09:08,610 --> 00:09:13,077
Well, it certainly doesn't look like a murder case, but...

156
00:09:13,661 --> 00:09:16,375
I suppose we should hear what happened.

157
00:09:16,459 --> 00:09:17,544
Ye... yes.

158
00:09:18,296 --> 00:09:23,431
About an hour ago, I had a huge fight with my wife, Chiyoko.

159
00:09:23,514 --> 00:09:25,978
To let her cool down, I left her alone

160
00:09:26,062 --> 00:09:30,153
and decided to step outside with the housekeeper.

161
00:09:30,487 --> 00:09:31,739
That's right.

162
00:09:31,823 --> 00:09:33,911
Yes. We hadn't bought

163
00:09:33,994 --> 00:09:35,747
the ingredients for dinner yet,

164
00:09:35,831 --> 00:09:38,461
so I went to the nearby supermarket with the master.

165
00:09:39,254 --> 00:09:42,469
My wife broke her wrist and couldn't do housework,

166
00:09:42,552 --> 00:09:47,187
so we reluctantly hired a housekeeper, but she had another hysterical fit and started throwing things—

167
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:50,735
I was worried her injury would get worse.

168
00:09:50,820 --> 00:09:53,867
My eye was also in this condition.

169
00:09:53,951 --> 00:09:56,580
What happened to that bruise?

170
00:09:56,664 --> 00:09:59,336
When my wife gets angry, she often throws things.

171
00:09:59,420 --> 00:10:02,718
Thanks to that, I had to take the day off from work today.

172
00:10:02,801 --> 00:10:06,559
So... when you came back, your wife had committed suicide?

173
00:10:06,642 --> 00:10:10,150
No. We finished shopping in about 30 minutes,

174
00:10:10,233 --> 00:10:13,824
came back with the master, and when we opened the front door,

175
00:10:13,907 --> 00:10:17,456
we heard the door to this bedroom slam shut.

176
00:10:17,789 --> 00:10:21,130
So I thought she was still alive at that point.

177
00:10:21,213 --> 00:10:25,722
We knocked on the door and called out to her, but there was no answer.

178
00:10:25,805 --> 00:10:28,144
It seemed she was still angry.

179
00:10:28,227 --> 00:10:31,317
So I had the housekeeper make some coffee,

180
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:34,281
and after about 30 minutes of small talk...

181
00:10:34,364 --> 00:10:36,828
we knocked on the bedroom door again.

182
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:39,082
When we went inside...

183
00:10:39,708 --> 00:10:42,631
this is what we found.

184
00:10:43,007 --> 00:10:47,182
I never imagined a simple argument would make my wife so distraught.

185
00:10:47,265 --> 00:10:50,480
I see... So?

186
00:10:52,234 --> 00:10:54,655
This note at the wife's feet?

187
00:10:55,114 --> 00:10:57,954
It's a suicide note. It's in my wife's own handwriting.

188
00:10:58,037 --> 00:11:01,335
She wrote about my injury, our son's exam,

189
00:11:01,418 --> 00:11:05,051
and even about my sister's daughter, who will be celebrating her Shichi-Go-San this year.

190
00:11:05,134 --> 00:11:07,556
She wrote about all of them.

191
00:11:07,849 --> 00:11:11,730
"Please forgive me for leaving you so suddenly."

192
00:11:11,815 --> 00:11:13,609
(Crying)

193
00:11:13,693 --> 00:11:16,156
This is clearly a suicide.

194
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,450
No. Hmm?

195
00:11:17,869 --> 00:11:20,123
It might be murder. Huh?

196
00:11:20,206 --> 00:11:21,417
Huh?

197
00:11:22,377 --> 00:11:23,462
That suicide note—

198
00:11:23,922 --> 00:11:28,264
she would have written it in that notebook on the desk and torn it out, right?

199
00:11:28,849 --> 00:11:32,439
But look closely. The middle binding ring still has

200
00:11:32,522 --> 00:11:36,780
the torn remains from the two holes at the bottom of the notebook,

201
00:11:37,073 --> 00:11:41,415
but the note has three torn holes. Don't you think that's strange?

202
00:11:41,498 --> 00:11:43,669
Wait, seriously?

203
00:11:43,962 --> 00:11:45,673
Y... you're right.

204
00:11:45,925 --> 00:11:49,598
Besides, the handwriting on the note is quite distorted.

205
00:11:50,016 --> 00:11:52,437
See, your wife seems to have used that notebook

206
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:54,984
to leave messages often,

207
00:11:55,068 --> 00:11:58,699
but she always ended them by writing only her first name.

208
00:11:59,534 --> 00:12:03,334
Yet, this note has her full name written on it.

209
00:12:04,127 --> 00:12:06,340
That seems very strange to me.

210
00:12:07,258 --> 00:12:09,054
That's true.

211
00:12:09,137 --> 00:12:11,517
Was the front door locked?

212
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:12,853
Ah, yes.

213
00:12:13,229 --> 00:12:16,193
I was the one who opened it, and it was properly locked.

214
00:12:16,276 --> 00:12:18,322
Then who has spare keys?

215
00:12:18,406 --> 00:12:23,374
Only myself, my wife, the housekeeper, and our son, Yasue.

216
00:12:23,457 --> 00:12:25,211
Where is your son now?

217
00:12:25,294 --> 00:12:27,842
I think he's at driving school.

218
00:12:27,925 --> 00:12:30,221
He said he has an exam soon.

219
00:12:30,304 --> 00:12:34,438
Ah... also, there's supposedly a spare key

220
00:12:34,521 --> 00:12:36,567
kept in the mailbox on the first floor.

221
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:40,283
That mailbox has a lock on it, of course?

222
00:12:40,366 --> 00:12:42,495
Yes, it's a combination lock.

223
00:12:42,579 --> 00:12:45,418
I didn't think anyone else could open it easily...

224
00:12:45,752 --> 00:12:49,969
Left 7, right 2, then left 3.

225
00:12:50,053 --> 00:12:53,852
Ah! There's one more person. Someone who knows

226
00:12:53,935 --> 00:12:55,480
the combination. Huh?

227
00:12:55,772 --> 00:12:59,822
Yesterday, when I was trying to get the mail from that mailbox,

228
00:12:59,906 --> 00:13:02,577
I forgot the note with the combination and was struggling,

229
00:13:02,660 --> 00:13:04,957
and that person told me the numbers.

230
00:13:05,041 --> 00:13:08,089
H... how does he know the combination?

231
00:13:08,172 --> 00:13:11,595
When you tried to open the mailbox before,

232
00:13:11,678 --> 00:13:14,392
you dropped the note with the combination, right?

233
00:13:14,476 --> 00:13:18,025
I picked it up. Don't you remember?

234
00:13:18,109 --> 00:13:21,240
B... but that was just a moment—

235
00:13:21,323 --> 00:13:24,204
I don't think even a second passed.

236
00:13:24,287 --> 00:13:26,960
That's plenty of time for me.

237
00:13:27,043 --> 00:13:29,339
I'm good at remembering things like that.

238
00:13:29,422 --> 00:13:30,466
Huh?

239
00:13:30,550 --> 00:13:33,849
Maybe the best in Japan... no, in the world.

240
00:13:36,186 --> 00:13:38,440
Is that person a resident of this mansion?

241
00:13:38,524 --> 00:13:41,363
Y... yes. He's the neighbor.

242
00:13:41,446 --> 00:13:44,411
He always has an unshaven beard and is kind of unkempt.

243
00:13:44,786 --> 00:13:46,875
I think his name was...

244
00:13:47,167 --> 00:13:49,045
If he's next door, it's faster to just go.

245
00:13:49,129 --> 00:13:50,924
Uh... yeah. Ah, hey...

246
00:13:51,008 --> 00:13:52,427
(Door opens) Hmm?

247
00:13:54,306 --> 00:13:55,893
Wha... wait a minute.

248
00:13:55,976 --> 00:13:58,230
(Doorbell) Huh?

249
00:13:59,817 --> 00:14:01,403
Yes. What is it?

250
00:14:01,695 --> 00:14:03,407
Hmm? Ah!

251
00:14:03,699 --> 00:14:04,911
Ah!

252
00:14:04,994 --> 00:14:07,665
Ah! Yumi-tan!

253
00:14:07,749 --> 00:14:10,421
Huh? Yu... Yumi-tan?

254
00:14:10,923 --> 00:14:12,425
So you know him?

255
00:14:12,508 --> 00:14:14,095
Uh... yes.

256
00:14:17,727 --> 00:14:19,189
He's my ex-boyfriend.

257
00:14:22,876 --> 00:14:24,212
Huh?!"

258
00:14:24,505 --> 00:14:28,513
Ha, ahaha, haha...

259
00:14:33,188 --> 00:14:35,902
So, to summarize the situation...

260
00:14:35,986 --> 00:14:39,743
To let his angry wife cool down,

261
00:14:39,827 --> 00:14:44,753
the husband went grocery shopping with the housekeeper for about 30 minutes...

262
00:14:44,837 --> 00:14:47,759
When they returned and opened the front door,

263
00:14:48,010 --> 00:14:51,349
they heard the door to this bedroom close.

264
00:14:51,434 --> 00:14:54,022
They knocked and called out, but there was no answer.

265
00:14:54,355 --> 00:14:57,153
So they waited another 30 minutes,

266
00:14:57,236 --> 00:15:00,660
chatting with the housekeeper in the kitchen to pass the time...

267
00:15:01,077 --> 00:15:05,044
Then they knocked again, and this time when they entered,

268
00:15:05,127 --> 00:15:07,131
the wife, Chiyoko-san, had hanged herself

269
00:15:07,214 --> 00:15:09,553
with an electrical cord.

270
00:15:09,637 --> 00:15:10,680
Yes.

271
00:15:11,056 --> 00:15:13,478
What caused the argument?

272
00:15:13,561 --> 00:15:14,605
Stocks.

273
00:15:14,688 --> 00:15:17,193
Stocks? Hmm?

274
00:15:17,945 --> 00:15:20,951
My wife has been really into stocks lately.

275
00:15:21,034 --> 00:15:23,498
When I told her to be careful, she had a fit.

276
00:15:23,581 --> 00:15:25,292
I see.

277
00:15:25,376 --> 00:15:28,424
Well, our son, who's about to graduate from university,

278
00:15:28,508 --> 00:15:30,762
hasn't been able to find a job yet,

279
00:15:30,845 --> 00:15:34,310
so I think the stress was also a factor.

280
00:15:34,394 --> 00:15:35,939
So you have a son?

281
00:15:36,022 --> 00:15:37,024
Yes.

282
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:40,991
But since he started living alone in an apartment near his university,

283
00:15:41,074 --> 00:15:43,203
he rarely comes to visit.

284
00:15:43,286 --> 00:15:46,292
Ah, but he did call the other day.

285
00:15:46,877 --> 00:15:50,134
He said that once he gets his license, he wants me to buy him a car,

286
00:15:50,217 --> 00:15:52,639
so he'll bring a catalog next time.

287
00:15:52,723 --> 00:15:54,810
I see, a catalog.

288
00:15:54,893 --> 00:15:56,062
But my wife

289
00:15:56,146 --> 00:15:59,778
yelled that a car is out of the question when he hasn't even found a job yet,

290
00:15:59,862 --> 00:16:02,492
and hung up on him.

291
00:16:02,576 --> 00:16:06,417
Oh? You're... from that optical illusion case, aren't you?

292
00:16:06,667 --> 00:16:10,592
Yes. My workplace turned into another incident like this...

293
00:16:10,675 --> 00:16:13,263
Haah... Just make sure you don't end up like Mouri-kun,

294
00:16:13,346 --> 00:16:15,643
someone who attracts death.

295
00:16:15,727 --> 00:16:17,021
In... Inspector.

296
00:16:17,564 --> 00:16:18,570
(Clears throat)

297
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:22,824
But why did the report come from Traffic Division's Miike-kun?

298
00:16:22,908 --> 00:16:24,368
Ah, that's...

299
00:16:24,703 --> 00:16:28,043
Sakurako-san saw the body and called her friend,

300
00:16:28,126 --> 00:16:31,257
Police Officer Miike Naeko.

301
00:16:31,341 --> 00:16:34,848
When I heard about it, I came here too.

302
00:16:34,932 --> 00:16:36,435
Co... Conan-kun.

303
00:16:37,019 --> 00:16:40,819
No wonder the kids were at the front door.

304
00:16:41,277 --> 00:16:44,993
But Conan-kun, how did you get inside this mansion?

305
00:16:45,244 --> 00:16:48,793
There was someone with children entering the mansion,

306
00:16:48,876 --> 00:16:51,799
so I pretended to be their friend's friend and went in.

307
00:16:51,882 --> 00:16:53,803
Th... that's not good.

308
00:16:53,886 --> 00:16:55,264
...Geez.

309
00:16:55,347 --> 00:16:59,272
So, Naeko, was the housekeeper your classmate?

310
00:16:59,355 --> 00:17:03,196
No, she's a childhood friend who lived in my neighborhood.

311
00:17:03,823 --> 00:17:07,079
I'm one year older than Sakurako.

312
00:17:07,163 --> 00:17:08,206
Hmm?

313
00:17:09,041 --> 00:17:12,089
Well, anyway, only the husband,

314
00:17:12,173 --> 00:17:15,345
wife, and housekeeper were here, correct?

315
00:17:15,430 --> 00:17:19,103
Yes. I haven't seen my son in over a year.

316
00:17:19,187 --> 00:17:23,654
Hmm... Then who is the man behind Yumi-kun?

317
00:17:23,738 --> 00:17:26,075
Hmm? Ah, this is...

318
00:17:26,577 --> 00:17:29,165
I live next door.

319
00:17:29,248 --> 00:17:30,292
Yumi-ta... Hmm!

320
00:17:30,375 --> 00:17:32,087
Ah, I am currently

321
00:17:32,171 --> 00:17:33,966
going out with Yumi-san.

322
00:17:34,050 --> 00:17:35,762
My name is Shukichi Haneda.

323
00:17:35,845 --> 00:17:36,931
Huh? Huh?

324
00:17:37,014 --> 00:17:41,105
He's my ex-boyfriend. We already broke up.

325
00:17:41,649 --> 00:17:44,905
B-but why is your boyfriend here?

326
00:17:44,988 --> 00:17:48,161
Ah... this "ex" boyfriend

327
00:17:48,245 --> 00:17:50,082
said he remembered the combination for the mailbox

328
00:17:50,165 --> 00:17:53,714
that had the spare key to this room, so I dragged him here.

329
00:17:53,798 --> 00:17:57,388
Huh? I feel like I've seen you somewhere before too.

330
00:17:57,472 --> 00:18:00,310
Come to think of it, I feel like I've heard that name too.

331
00:18:00,394 --> 00:18:04,402
Hmm? Don't tell me you saw it on a wanted poster?

332
00:18:04,486 --> 00:18:05,822
Don't be stupid.

333
00:18:05,905 --> 00:18:07,324
Hmm... Ahaha.

334
00:18:07,909 --> 00:18:11,542
But well, there's a suicide note at the victim's feet,

335
00:18:11,625 --> 00:18:13,336
so it's probably a suicide.

336
00:18:13,421 --> 00:18:17,011
Ah, but Conan-kun said

337
00:18:17,303 --> 00:18:19,348
that it might not be a suicide.

338
00:18:19,433 --> 00:18:21,729
What? Hmph.

339
00:18:24,484 --> 00:18:26,697
I see. Th... that's true.

340
00:18:27,615 --> 00:18:30,705
The torn edges of this note and the notebook don't match.

341
00:18:31,289 --> 00:18:33,126
The note says:

342
00:18:33,209 --> 00:18:38,053
"I'm sorry for injuring you. I pray for your speedy recovery."

343
00:18:38,512 --> 00:18:42,979
"Yasue-san, do your best on your exam. I know you'll pass."

344
00:18:43,063 --> 00:18:45,359
"For Ichiko-chan's Shichi-Go-San,

345
00:18:45,443 --> 00:18:48,365
please dress her in my furisode."

346
00:18:48,449 --> 00:18:51,497
"Please forgive me for leaving you so suddenly."

347
00:18:51,580 --> 00:18:53,459
"Itami Chiyoko."

348
00:18:54,377 --> 00:18:57,049
Is there anything suspicious about this content?

349
00:18:57,132 --> 00:18:58,427
Uh... yes.

350
00:18:58,969 --> 00:19:01,349
As you can see, last night

351
00:19:01,433 --> 00:19:04,021
my wife threw an ashtray that hit me in the eye,

352
00:19:04,105 --> 00:19:06,109
leaving this bruise.

353
00:19:06,192 --> 00:19:08,029
And my son, Yasue, said he has

354
00:19:08,113 --> 00:19:11,244
his written driver's license exam soon.

355
00:19:11,495 --> 00:19:14,166
Also, my sister's daughter

356
00:19:14,250 --> 00:19:16,422
is turning seven this year, so...

357
00:19:16,505 --> 00:19:18,592
Shichi-Go-San, then.

358
00:19:18,676 --> 00:19:20,596
But why the ashtray?

359
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:23,644
When my wife gets angry, she often throws things.

360
00:19:23,727 --> 00:19:26,190
I saw that too.

361
00:19:26,274 --> 00:19:30,992
So I thought the cell phone found in front of the bedroom might have been thrown by her as well.

362
00:19:31,075 --> 00:19:33,163
There was a cell phone on the floor?

363
00:19:33,246 --> 00:19:34,833
Huh? Yes.

364
00:19:35,375 --> 00:19:36,962
When we returned from shopping

365
00:19:37,045 --> 00:19:40,636
and first knocked on the bedroom door, I noticed it.

366
00:19:40,928 --> 00:19:42,932
Where is that phone now?

367
00:19:43,016 --> 00:19:45,187
I have it. Hmm?

368
00:19:45,771 --> 00:19:49,028
I was planning to give it back once she calmed down.

369
00:19:49,946 --> 00:19:54,371
Hmm... It doesn't look like there are any calls or messages from today.

370
00:19:54,789 --> 00:19:59,298
If this was a murder, I thought it might have been used in some trick,

371
00:19:59,381 --> 00:20:01,970
but it seems unrelated to the case.

372
00:20:02,054 --> 00:20:05,352
But still, the lady of the house didn't commit suicide after all.

373
00:20:05,436 --> 00:20:07,314
Hmm? "After all"?

374
00:20:07,397 --> 00:20:10,070
Because she said so herself.

375
00:20:10,153 --> 00:20:14,036
"I am loved by God. I'm a lucky person."

376
00:20:14,119 --> 00:20:16,040
A lucky person?

377
00:20:16,123 --> 00:20:17,251
What do you mean?

378
00:20:17,544 --> 00:20:21,969
Years ago, the plane my wife was on nearly crashed,

379
00:20:22,052 --> 00:20:24,933
but miraculously, she survived.

380
00:20:25,016 --> 00:20:26,018
Oh?

381
00:20:26,102 --> 00:20:28,314
So were you on that plane too?

382
00:20:28,398 --> 00:20:31,572
Ah, no. I was supposed to go,

383
00:20:31,655 --> 00:20:35,245
but I broke my leg on a ski trip right before.

384
00:20:35,580 --> 00:20:38,167
So a wife like that, just because of an argument,

385
00:20:38,251 --> 00:20:40,590
I can't imagine her committing suicide.

386
00:20:40,673 --> 00:20:44,263
But that was just something she always said.

387
00:20:44,346 --> 00:20:46,977
Besides, that suicide note is also strange.

388
00:20:47,060 --> 00:20:48,396
Huh? In what way?

389
00:20:48,939 --> 00:20:50,275
The lady of the house...

390
00:20:50,358 --> 00:20:54,325
caught a bad cold when she was seven and couldn't do her Shichi-Go-San,

391
00:20:54,408 --> 00:20:56,287
and she told me that she had no connection to kimono

392
00:20:56,370 --> 00:20:59,335
until her Coming of Age ceremony.

393
00:20:59,419 --> 00:21:02,592
Huh? Hmph... I see.

394
00:21:02,675 --> 00:21:04,178
Hmm? Hmm?

395
00:21:07,392 --> 00:21:12,110
So that's what you meant by "the one outfit you prepared"?

396
00:21:13,071 --> 00:21:15,075
What are you talking about, Chuukichi?

397
00:21:15,158 --> 00:21:17,329
I told you, she didn't have a kimono made.

398
00:21:17,413 --> 00:21:19,375
Th... that's why I said it's Shukichi.

399
00:21:19,668 --> 00:21:21,546
How many times do I have to tell you I'm not Chuukichi?

400
00:21:21,630 --> 00:21:23,884
Chuukichi suits you better.

401
00:21:23,967 --> 00:21:25,846
Looking so unkempt...

402
00:21:26,515 --> 00:21:29,269
"The one outfit you prepared."

403
00:21:29,353 --> 00:21:31,273
That's... if I remember correctly...

404
00:21:31,650 --> 00:21:34,154
Ah, I see.

405
00:21:34,238 --> 00:21:37,745
If you think about it that way, even the unnatural parts of that note...

406
00:21:38,539 --> 00:21:41,753
We still don't have enough for the full picture,

407
00:21:41,837 --> 00:21:44,592
but if we piece it together one move at a time...

408
00:21:46,763 --> 00:21:48,224
Right?

409
00:21:49,143 --> 00:21:51,230
Shukichi Haneda-san.

410
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:56,742
Hmm... This suicide note is still suspicious.

411
00:21:56,825 --> 00:22:00,290
Yes, it seems we need a handwriting analysis.

412
00:22:00,373 --> 00:22:04,966
Ah, and it also bothers me that someone

413
00:22:05,049 --> 00:22:07,930
with a broken wrist would choose hanging,

414
00:22:08,014 --> 00:22:11,480
which is difficult to do with one hand, as a method of suicide.

415
00:22:11,563 --> 00:22:13,065
That's true. (Door opens)

416
00:22:13,149 --> 00:22:14,486
Chief Megure. Hmm?

417
00:22:14,986 --> 00:22:17,365
We have an eyewitness account of a suspicious person.

418
00:22:17,450 --> 00:22:19,077
What? Hmm?

419
00:22:19,621 --> 00:22:22,375
According to the concierge in the first floor lobby,

420
00:22:22,460 --> 00:22:25,466
a suspicious person with their face hidden by a hat, mask, and glasses

421
00:22:25,549 --> 00:22:27,678
entered and left the mansion.

422
00:22:33,064 --> 00:22:39,076
♪~♪

423
00:23:46,962 --> 00:23:52,807
♪~♪

424
00:23:52,890 --> 00:23:55,479
Wow! Chi... Chiba-kun. Huh?

425
00:23:55,813 --> 00:23:57,858
Let go, ugh...

426
00:23:57,942 --> 00:24:00,154
It's not like I'm suspicious or anything...

427
00:24:00,656 --> 00:24:03,369
They say the culprit returns to the scene.

428
00:24:03,453 --> 00:24:05,708
Before you found the wife's phone,

429
00:24:05,791 --> 00:24:08,672
you heard the bedroom door close,

430
00:24:08,755 --> 00:24:10,299
didn't you, Sakurako-san?

431
00:24:10,383 --> 00:24:11,385
Uh... yes.

432
00:24:11,928 --> 00:24:13,389
You can't say that.

433
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:16,813
It's a woman. You were meeting some woman, weren't you?

434
00:24:16,939 --> 00:24:18,239
Next Conan,

435
00:24:18,239 --> 00:24:22,139
"The Neighbor at the Site is an Ex-Boyfriend (Part 2)"

436
00:24:37,939 --> 00:24:40,439
Next Conan's Hint:

437
00:24:40,439 --> 00:24:42,539
"Cell phone cover".

434
00:24:42,761 --> 00:24:44,139
Chuukichi? Yumi-tan!

438
00:24:44,222 --> 00:24:45,266
That's what you're interested in?

439
00:24:45,350 --> 00:24:47,395
Another new couple, huh?
